{
    "info": {
        "name": "Sellio Metrics API",
        "description": "Event-driven developer scoring API for the Sellio Squad.\n\nDeployed on Cloudflare Workers with D1 database for event storage.\n\nAuthentication: None required (GitHub App auth handled server-side).\n\nAPI v2 (Event-Driven):\n- Events stored in D1 as immutable facts\n- Scores computed via SQL JOIN with dynamic point rules\n- Leaderboard precomputed every 6 hours via Cron Trigger\n- Attendance tracking with CHECK_IN/CHECK_OUT duration scoring",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "variable": [
        {
            "key": "baseUrl",
            "value": "https://sellio-metrics.abdoessam743.workers.dev",
            "description": "Production Worker URL"
        },
        {
            "key": "localUrl",
            "value": "http://localhost:8787",
            "description": "Local development URL (wrangler dev)"
        },
        {
            "key": "org",
            "value": "Sellio-Squad"
        },
        {
            "key": "repo",
            "value": "sellio_mobile"
        }
    ],
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "Health",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Ping",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ping",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "ping"]
                        },
                        "description": "Simple ping endpoint. Returns { pong: true, time } — no auth needed."
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"pong\": true,\n  \"time\": \"2026-03-12T00:00:00.000Z\"\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Health Check",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "health"]
                        },
                        "description": "Returns server health status, org name, D1 availability, GitHub rate limit, and timestamp."
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"org\": \"Sellio-Squad\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-12T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"githubRateLimit\": {\n    \"remaining\": 5000,\n    \"limit\": 5000,\n    \"resetAt\": \"\",\n    \"isLow\": false\n  },\n  \"d1Available\": true\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Point Rules",
            "description": "Manage dynamic scoring rules. Changes persist in D1 and KV (no TTL). Changing rules auto-invalidates all cached scores.",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Get Point Rules",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/points/rules",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "points", "rules"]
                        },
                        "description": "Returns all point rules.\n\nReads from SCORES_KV (fast), falls back to D1.\n\nDefault rules:\n- PR_CREATED: 3 points\n- PR_MERGED: 2 points\n- PR_REVIEW: 0 points\n- COMMENT: 1 point\n- CHECK_IN: 2 points\n- CHECK_OUT: 0 points\n- ATTENDANCE_DURATION: 1 point (per 15-min block)"
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"rules\": [\n    { \"eventType\": \"PR_CREATED\", \"points\": 3, \"description\": \"Developer created a pull request\", \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-12 00:00:00\" },\n    { \"eventType\": \"PR_MERGED\", \"points\": 2, \"description\": \"Pull request was merged\", \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-12 00:00:00\" },\n    { \"eventType\": \"PR_REVIEW\", \"points\": 0, \"description\": \"Developer reviewed a pull request\", \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-12 00:00:00\" },\n    { \"eventType\": \"COMMENT\", \"points\": 1, \"description\": \"Developer left a comment on a PR\", \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-12 00:00:00\" },\n    { \"eventType\": \"CHECK_IN\", \"points\": 2, \"description\": \"Developer checked in\", \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-12 00:00:00\" },\n    { \"eventType\": \"CHECK_OUT\", \"points\": 0, \"description\": \"Developer checked out\", \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-12 00:00:00\" },\n    { \"eventType\": \"ATTENDANCE_DURATION\", \"points\": 1, \"description\": \"Per 15-minute block\", \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-12 00:00:00\" }\n  ]\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Update Point Rule",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "PUT",
                        "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"eventType\": \"PR_REVIEW\",\n  \"points\": 2,\n  \"description\": \"Developer reviewed a pull request\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/points/rules",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "points", "rules"]
                        },
                        "description": "Update a specific point rule.\n\nWrites to D1 and syncs to KV. Invalidates ALL cached scores.\nChange is logged for audit.\n\nBody:\n- eventType (string, required): e.g. PR_REVIEW\n- points (number, required): new point value\n- description (string, optional): rule description"
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"rule\": { \"eventType\": \"PR_REVIEW\", \"points\": 2, \"description\": \"Developer reviewed a pull request\", \"updatedAt\": \"2026-03-12 00:00:00\" }\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Scores",
            "description": "Event-driven leaderboard from D1. Uses SQL JOIN with point_rules for dynamic scoring.",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Get Leaderboard",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/scores/leaderboard",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "scores", "leaderboard"],
                            "query": [
                                {"key": "since", "value": "2026-03-01T00:00:00Z", "description": "ISO 8601 start date (optional)", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "until", "value": "2026-03-31T23:59:59Z", "description": "ISO 8601 end date (optional)", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "limit", "value": "10", "description": "Max entries (default: 10)", "disabled": true}
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "Returns aggregated leaderboard from D1 events.\n\nScores computed via:\nSELECT e.developer_id, SUM(r.points)\nFROM events e JOIN point_rules r ON e.event_type = r.event_type\nGROUP BY e.developer_id ORDER BY total_points DESC\n\nResults cached in SCORES_KV (6h TTL). Precomputed every 6 hours by Cron Trigger."
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"entries\": [\n    {\n      \"developer_id\": \"dev-01\",\n      \"total_points\": 42,\n      \"event_counts\": {\n        \"PR_CREATED\": 8,\n        \"PR_MERGED\": 6,\n        \"COMMENT\": 12\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"developer_id\": \"dev-02\",\n      \"total_points\": 35,\n      \"event_counts\": {\n        \"PR_CREATED\": 5,\n        \"PR_MERGED\": 4,\n        \"PR_REVIEW\": 10\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"cachedAt\": \"2026-03-12T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"since\": null,\n  \"until\": null\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Events",
            "description": "Browse raw scoring events stored in D1. Events are immutable and have no TTL.",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "List Events",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/events",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "events"],
                            "query": [
                                {"key": "developerId", "value": "dev-01", "description": "Filter by developer (optional)", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "eventType", "value": "PR_CREATED", "description": "Filter by event type (optional)", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "since", "value": "2026-03-01T00:00:00Z", "description": "ISO 8601 start (optional)", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "until", "value": "2026-03-31T23:59:59Z", "description": "ISO 8601 end (optional)", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "limit", "value": "50", "description": "Max events (default: 50)", "disabled": true}
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "List raw scoring events from D1.\n\nEvents are immutable (no TTL, no deletion). Each event has a unique deterministic ID for idempotency.\n\nEvent types: PR_CREATED, PR_MERGED, PR_REVIEW, COMMENT, CHECK_IN, CHECK_OUT, ATTENDANCE_DURATION"
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"count\": 2,\n  \"events\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"github:pr_created:Sellio-Squad/sellio_mobile:42:dev-01\",\n      \"developer_id\": \"dev-01\",\n      \"event_type\": \"PR_CREATED\",\n      \"source\": \"github\",\n      \"source_id\": \"https://github.com/Sellio-Squad/sellio_mobile/pull/42\",\n      \"event_timestamp\": \"2026-03-10T14:30:00.000Z\",\n      \"created_at\": \"2026-03-10T14:30:05.000Z\",\n      \"metadata\": \"{\\\"pr_number\\\":42,\\\"title\\\":\\\"feat: new feature\\\",\\\"repo\\\":\\\"Sellio-Squad/sellio_mobile\\\"}\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Attendance",
            "description": "CHECK_IN / CHECK_OUT tracking with duration-based scoring.\n\nDuration calculated on CHECK_OUT → generates ATTENDANCE_DURATION event scored per 15-minute block.",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Check In",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"developerId\": \"dev-01\",\n  \"checkin_time\": \"2026-03-12T09:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"meeting_id\": \"daily-standup-0312\",\n  \"location\": \"Room A\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/check-in",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "attendance", "check-in"]
                        },
                        "description": "Register a CHECK_IN event.\n\nRequired: developerId (string)\nOptional: checkin_time (ISO 8601, defaults to now), meeting_id, location\n\nAll timestamps validated as ISO 8601 and normalized to UTC."
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"eventId\": \"checkin:dev-01:2026-03-12T09:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"inserted\": true\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Check Out",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"developerId\": \"dev-01\",\n  \"checkout_time\": \"2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z\",\n  \"meeting_id\": \"daily-standup-0312\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/check-out",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "attendance", "check-out"]
                        },
                        "description": "Register a CHECK_OUT event.\n\nAutomatically:\n1. Finds matching CHECK_IN from ATTENDANCE_KV\n2. Calculates duration in minutes\n3. Creates ATTENDANCE_DURATION event (scored per 15-min block)\n\nOrphan handling: CHECK_OUT without matching CHECK_IN → logged as warning, no ATTENDANCE_DURATION generated."
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK (with duration)",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"eventId\": \"checkout:dev-01:2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z\",\n  \"inserted\": true,\n  \"durationMinutes\": 90\n}"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK (orphan)",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"eventId\": \"checkout:dev-01:2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z\",\n  \"inserted\": true,\n  \"warning\": \"No matching CHECK_IN found — CHECK_OUT recorded but no ATTENDANCE_DURATION generated\"\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Attendance History",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "GET",
                        "header": [],
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/attendance/history",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "attendance", "history"],
                            "query": [
                                {"key": "developerId", "value": "dev-01", "description": "Filter by developer (optional)", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "since", "value": "2026-03-01T00:00:00Z", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "until", "value": "2026-03-31T23:59:59Z", "disabled": true},
                                {"key": "limit", "value": "50", "disabled": true}
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "Get attendance event history from D1. Returns CHECK_IN, CHECK_OUT, and ATTENDANCE_DURATION events."
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"count\": 3,\n  \"events\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"duration:dev-01:2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z\",\n      \"developer_id\": \"dev-01\",\n      \"event_type\": \"ATTENDANCE_DURATION\",\n      \"source\": \"attendance\",\n      \"event_timestamp\": \"2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z\",\n      \"metadata\": \"{\\\"checkin_time\\\":\\\"2026-03-12T09:00:00.000Z\\\",\\\"checkout_time\\\":\\\"2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z\\\",\\\"duration_minutes\\\":90,\\\"duration_blocks\\\":6}\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "GitHub Sync",
            "description": "Backfill D1 with historical data from GitHub API. Call once per repo to populate events, then let webhooks handle real-time.",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Sync Repository",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"repo\": \"sellio_mobile\",\n  \"owner\": \"Sellio-Squad\"\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/sync/github",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "sync", "github"]
                        },
                        "description": "Fetches all PRs from a GitHub repo and creates scoring events in D1.\n\nThis is the backfill mechanism:\n1. Fetches PRs from GitHub API (fresh, no cache)\n2. Creates PR_CREATED, PR_MERGED, PR_REVIEW, COMMENT events\n3. All events are idempotent (duplicate calls safe)\n4. Precomputes leaderboard snapshots after sync\n\nBody:\n- repo (string, required): repository name\n- owner (string, optional): defaults to configured org"
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"repo\": \"Sellio-Squad/sellio_mobile\",\n  \"prsFound\": 42,\n  \"eventsGenerated\": 156,\n  \"eventsInserted\": 156,\n  \"duplicates\": 0\n}"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK (re-run, idempotent)",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"repo\": \"Sellio-Squad/sellio_mobile\",\n  \"prsFound\": 42,\n  \"eventsGenerated\": 156,\n  \"eventsInserted\": 0,\n  \"duplicates\": 156\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Webhooks",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "GitHub Webhook",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [
                            {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"},
                            {"key": "X-GitHub-Event", "value": "pull_request", "description": "Event type: pull_request | pull_request_review | issue_comment"},
                            {"key": "X-GitHub-Delivery", "value": "{{$guid}}"}
                        ],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n  \"action\": \"opened\",\n  \"pull_request\": {\n    \"number\": 42,\n    \"title\": \"feat: new feature\",\n    \"html_url\": \"https://github.com/Sellio-Squad/sellio_mobile/pull/42\",\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-03-12T10:00:00Z\",\n    \"user\": { \"login\": \"dev-01\" }\n  },\n  \"repository\": { \"full_name\": \"Sellio-Squad/sellio_mobile\" }\n}"
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/webhooks/github",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["api", "webhooks", "github"]
                        },
                        "description": "GitHub webhook for real-time event-driven scoring.\n\nWhen GitHub sends an event, this endpoint:\n1. Ingests events into D1 with deterministic IDs (idempotent)\n2. Invalidates affected developer's score cache\n\nEvent types:\n- pull_request (opened) → PR_CREATED\n- pull_request (closed+merged) → PR_MERGED\n- pull_request_review → PR_REVIEW\n- issue_comment / review_comment → COMMENT"
                    },
                    "response": [
                        {
                            "name": "200 OK",
                            "status": "OK",
                            "code": 200,
                            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                            "body": "{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"event\": \"pull_request\",\n  \"repo\": \"Sellio-Squad/sellio_mobile\",\n  \"invalidated\": true,\n  \"eventsIngested\": 1,\n  \"duplicates\": 0\n}"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
